HEADWORD: Southerner
<hw>South"ern*er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An inhabitant or
native of the south, esp. of the Southern States of North America;
opposed to <contr>Northerner</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Southernliness</ent>⟦br⟧
